# Project Rules (paste into your project rules / .cursorrules / agent rules)

## Tech Stack
- Use Next.js (App Router), React, and TypeScript for all code.
- Prefer functional components.

## Classnames Convention (MANDATORY)
- Always import the `classnames` package as `cn`:
  - `import cn from "classnames";`
- For any `className=...`, ALWAYS use `{cn()}` (never a raw string, never template literals).
- In `cn()`, ALWAYS pass individual class strings as separate arguments, separated by commas.
  - ✅ `className={cn("btn", "btnPrimary", isActive && "isActive")}`
  - ❌ `className="btn btnPrimary"`
  - ❌ `className={\`btn \${isActive ? "isActive" : ""}\`}`
  - ❌ `className={cn("btn btnPrimary")}`

## Examples
- `className={cn("card", "card--lg")}`
- `className={cn("navLink", pathname === "/apps" && "navLink--active")}`
